Brett Peter Cowan was convicted for the murder of 13-year-old Daniel Morcombe in 2003 . 
  Lawyers for Cowan will file an application to have Chief Justice Tim Carmody disqualified from hearing his appeal . 
  Cowan received a life sentence for murdering and indecently dealing with the body of the Sunshine Coast teenager . 
  His lawyers claim a child protection worker sent an email to Chief Justice Carmody that included a 'smiley face' The email was from Bravehearts and included a smiley face . 
  Daniel was abducted and murdered from a bus stop in December 2003 . 
 